This script takes a rhel4 kernel .spec file (maybe others) and generates
a git repository with each patch represented by a commit.

$ lftp ftp.redhat.com
> *hunt*
> get kernel-2.6.9-89.0.25.EL.src.rpm
$ alien -t kernel-2.6.9-89.0.25.EL.src.rpm
$ tar xjf linux-2.6.9-89.0.25.ELsmp.tar.bz2
$ tar xjf linux-2.6.9.tar.bz2
$ cd linux-2.6.9
$ git init
$ git add .
$ git commit -m linux-2.6.9
$ ..../kernel-spec-to-git < ../kernel-2.6.spec
$ git log
